{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}} {{Infobox person | name = Joanna Kos-Krauze | image = Kos Krauze Joanna.jpg | imagesize = | caption = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1972|12|8|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Olsztyn]], Poland | height = | death_date = | death_place = | birth_name = | occupation = [[Film director]], [[screenwriter]] | spouse = [[Krzysztof Krauze]] | othername = | homepage = | academyawards = }}
'''Joanna Kos-Krauze''' (born 8 December 1972),<ref>[http://www.filmpolski.pl/fp/index.php?osoba=1144944 ''Joanna Kos-Krauze''] at the Filmpolski Database {{pl}}</ref> credited also as '''Joanna Kos''', is a Polish film director and screenwriter, best known for her collaboration with her husband, [[Krzysztof Krauze]] (''[[My Nikifor]]'', ''[[Plac Zbawiciela (film)|Plac Zbawiciela]]'' /''Saviour square'').
In 2013 Joanna Kos and [[Krzysztof Krauze]] completed work on a biopic about the [[Romani people|Romani]] poet, [[Papusza]].<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2719094/?ref_=nm_flmg_wr_1 ''Papusza''] at the [[IMDb]]</ref>
